        <summary>How is Type II collagen different from Type I?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Type I is the collagen that makes up skin, bones, and tendons. Type II is the collagen specific to cartilage — the cushion inside your joints. For joint-focused support, Type II is the correct starting point.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can Skelecoll replace my joint-pain medication?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Skelecoll is a nutritional supplement, not a medication. It supports the structural tissues in your joints, but does not replace prescribed medication. Always consult your doctor before changing any treatment.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How soon until I feel a difference?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Most users report feeling less morning stiffness within 2–4 weeks. Structural improvements — reduced discomfort, better range of motion — typically come at 6–12 weeks. Consistency is everything.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is Skelecoll safe for older adults?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Not recommended for pregnant or lactating women, individuals below 18, or those with chronic liver/kidney diseases. Contains marine collagen (fish) — avoid if you have a fish or shellfish allergy. If you have any medical condition or are taking medication, consult your healthcare professional before use.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I take Skelecoll with Collabloom?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Yes. They're complementary — Collabloom focuses on skin/hair/nails and Skelecoll delivers bone, joint and muscle support. Many customers take both for full-body support. Do not exceed the recommended daily usage for each product.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Does Skelecoll contain allergens?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Contains fish and fish products (marine collagen). Sugar free, sweetened with Stevia. Cola flavour from natural food colours. Contains Class II preservatives. 40 kcal per 30ml shot, 10g protein. Not vegan.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How long should I take it?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Joint cartilage and connective tissues remodel slowly. Plan on a full 60–90 days of daily use to feel the structural difference. For best results, use consistently as directed.</div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

